.TH rtime 3
.SH NAME
rtime \- get remote time
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
.iX "rtime() function"
.nf
\*L#include <sys/types.h>\*O
\*L#include <sys/time.h>\*O
\*L#include <netinet/in.h>\*O
.PP
\*Lint rtime(addrp, timep, timeout)\*O
\*Lstruct sockaddr_in \(**addrp;\*O
\*Lstruct timeval \(**timep;\*O
\*Lstruct timeval \(**timeout;\*O
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
The \*Lrtime(\|)\*O function
consults the Internet Time Server at the address pointed to by
\*Vaddrp\*O
and returns the remote time in the
\*Ltimeval\*O
struct pointed to by
\*Vtimep\*O.
Normally, the UDP protocol is used when consulting the Time Server. The
\*Vtimeout\*O parameter specifies how long the routine should wait before giving
up when waiting for a reply.  If \*Vtimeout\*O is specified as NULL,
however, the routine will instead use TCP
and block until a reply is received from the time server.
.PP
The routine returns 0 if it is successful. Otherwise,
it returns \-1 and \*Lerrno\*O is set to reflect the cause of the error.
